These datasets are a sample collection of AccuWeather's enriched and comprehensive daily, 12-hour day-night, and hourly historical weather parameters. The sample contains one month of data for the top 50 global cities. Please note that this sample dataset represents a reduced portion of the available data attributes, volume, and data types available within AccuWeather's Data Suite and is intended for exploratory purposes rather than for production.

Some examples these datasets can be explored include:
- Compare weather conditions across the top 50 global cities to identify regional patterns in temperature, precipitation, and other weather parameters.
- Create visualizations like time series plots, heatmaps, or box plots to better understand the distribution and weather variability.
- Explore correlations between different weather parameters within and across cities to understand how they are related.
- Investigate temporal trends by analyzing how weather fluctuates over time.
- Identify outliers in the data that could indicate extreme weather occurrences.

With more access to AccuWeather's Data Suite available on the Databricks Marketplace, users can leverage weather information in a number of ways which include some of the following:

- **Economic Risk & Impact Analysis**: Utilize historical weather data to determine relationships on business metrics that are trained to predict potential impacts, such as supply chain disruptions, labor productivity, and transportation delays.
- **Energy Demand Planning & Forecasting**: Inform energy supply and production forecasts for wind, solar, and hydro installations by integrating historical weather information helping to optimize resource allocation and reduce operational risks.
- **Revenue Projections & Consumer Behavior Analysis**: Join historical weather data with past business data to create more accurate sales growth predictions, accounting for weather-driven demand.
- **Weather-Targeted Advertising**: Craft advertising campaigns by using historical and forecast weather data to reach consumers at the most critical times, maximizing interest and increasing conversion.

tables.name: claims_sample_synthetic

columns.name: hvid
columns.comment: The HealthVerity universal identifier for the patient, as determined by the HealthVerity matching engine.

columns.name: claim_id
columns.comment: Uniquely identifies a single claim that was submitted for reimbursement by this data vendor.

columns.name: claim_type
columns.comment: Indicates whether the claim is a professional (P) or institutional (I) claim.

columns.name: date_service
columns.comment: The calendar date on which the services referred to in this claim were rendered. (2400/DTP03, DTP01=472)

columns.name: diagnosis_code
columns.comment: A code indicating the patient's disease, injury, or condition, as identified by a healthcare practitioner. (2300/HI(01-12)-02)

columns.name: procedure_code
columns.comment: A code indicating the course of action taken by the healthcare practitioner. (837P 2400/SV101-02; 837I 2400/SV201, SV202)

columns.name: patient_gender
columns.comment: A single character identifying the gender of the person who received healthcare treatment. F = Female, M = Male, U = Unknown. (2010CA/DMG03)

columns.name: patient_year_of_birth
columns.comment: The four-digit year in which the patient was born. (2010CA/DMG02)

columns.name: patient_zip3
columns.comment: The first three digits of the U.S. postal code for the residence of the person who received healthcare treatment. If not supplied by the data provider, HealthVerity may populate this field with the first three digits of the postal code for the primary care provider or the rendering provider. (2010CA/N403)

columns.name: patient_state
columns.comment: The two-character postal code for the state in which the patient resides. (2010CA/N402)

columns.name: inst_admit_type_std_id
columns.comment: A standard code indicating the priority of this admission or visit. (837I 2300/CL101)

columns.name: inst_admit_source_std_id
columns.comment: A standard code indicating the source of the referral for the admission or visit. (837I 2300/CL102)

columns.name: inst_discharge_status_std_id
columns.comment: A standard code indicating the status of the patient as of the statement end date. (837I 2300/CL103)

columns.name: inst_type_of_bill_std_id
columns.comment: A standard code identifying the type of facility where services were performed. (837I 2300/CLM05-01, CLM05-03)

columns.name: inst_drg_std_id
columns.comment: A standard diagnosis-related group code indicating the payment classification. (837I 2300/HCP06)

columns.name: place_of_service_std_id
columns.comment: A standard code indicating the facility or place where services were rendered, as maintained by the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services (CMS). (2400/SV105)

columns.name: service_line_number
columns.comment: An integer representing the sequence for this service line within the claim. (2400/LX01)

columns.name: diagnosis_code_qual
columns.comment: The type of code used to indicate the disease, injury, or condition. Examples: ICD-10, ICD-9.

columns.name: admit_diagnosis_ind
columns.comment: A flag indicating whether the diagnosis reported on an institutional claim represents the admitting diagnosis. (2300/HI01-02)

columns.name: procedure_code_qual
columns.comment: The type of code used to indicate the course of action taken by the healthcare practitioner. Examples: CPT, HCPCS. (837P 2400/SV101-01; 837I 2400/SV202-01)

columns.name: procedure_units_billed
columns.comment: The number of discrete actions, elements, or precisely measured amounts administered in this course of action. (837P 2400/SV104; 837I 2400/SV205)

columns.name: procedure_modifier_1
columns.comment: Identifies the first qualifier for the procedure code. This is a code that supplies additional information about the procedure. (837P 2400/SV101-03; 837I 2400/SV202-03)

columns.name: procedure_modifier_2
columns.comment: Identifies the second qualifier for the procedure code. This is a code that supplies additional information about the procedure. (837P 2400/SV101-04; 837I 2400/SV202-04)

columns.name: procedure_modifier_3
columns.comment: Identifies the third qualifier for the procedure code. This is a code that supplies additional information about the procedure. (837P 2400/SV101-05; 837I 2400/SV202-05)

columns.name: procedure_modifier_4
columns.comment: Identifies the fourth qualifier for the procedure code. This is a code that supplies additional information about the procedure. (837P 2400/SV101-06; 837I 2400/SV202-06)

columns.name: revenue_code
columns.comment: A standard NUBC revenue code from the UB claim form. (837I 2400/SV201)

columns.name: line_charge
columns.comment: The total amount charged for this service line. (837P 2400/SV102; 837I 2400/SV203)

columns.name: line_allowed

payload.name: claims_sample_synthetic
payload.comment:
HealthVerity synchronizes transformational technologies with the nation’s largest healthcare and consumer data ecosystem to power previously unattainable outcomes and fundamentally advance science. HealthVerity offers hundreds of data sources across medical, pharmacy, lab, biomarker, EHR, consumer, and more.

This sample high-fidelity synthetic dataset from HealthVerity represents 1,500+ synthetic patients modeled on de-identified medical and pharmacy claims. **This dataset is intended for educational rather than production purposes, and may be used solely in non-production settings for internal testing, evaluation and/or informational purposes, and may not be relied upon or used for general commercial use**. This is only a synthetic sample dataset meant to illustrate a small portion of the type and volume of Real-world Data that is available within the HealthVerity Marketplace ecosystem. HealthVerity would welcome the opportunity to learn more about your project, and determine the optimal patient data for your objective. For more details on our offerings, please visit our website ([https://www.healthverity.com](https://www.healthverity.com)) or contact us through [https://www.healthverity.com/contact/](https://www.healthverity.com/contact/).

payload.name: hvid
payload.comment: The HealthVerity universal identifier for the patient, as determined by the HealthVerity matching engine.

payload.name: claim_id
payload.comment: Uniquely identifies a single claim that was submitted for reimbursement by this data vendor.

payload.name: claim_type
payload.comment: Indicates whether the claim is a professional (P) or institutional (I) claim.

payload.name: date_service
payload.comment: The calendar date on which the services referred to in this claim were rendered. (2400/DTP03, DTP01=472)

payload.name: diagnosis_code
payload.comment: A code indicating the patient's disease, injury, or condition, as identified by a healthcare practitioner. (2300/HI(01-12)-02)

payload.name: procedure_code
payload.comment: A code indicating the course of action taken by the healthcare practitioner. (837P 2400/SV101-02; 837I 2400/SV201, SV202)

payload.name: patient_gender
payload.comment: A single character identifying the gender of the person who received healthcare treatment. F = Female, M = Male, U = Unknown. (2010CA/DMG03)

payload.name: patient_year_of_birth
payload.comment: The four-digit year in which the patient was born. (2010CA/DMG02)

payload.name: patient_zip3
payload.comment: The first three digits of the U.S. postal code for the residence of the person who received healthcare treatment. If not supplied by the data provider, HealthVerity may populate this field with the first three digits of the postal code for the primary care provider or the rendering provider. (2010CA/N403)

payload.name: patient_state
payload.comment: The two-character postal code for the state in which the patient resides. (2010CA/N402)

payload.name: inst_admit_type_std_id
payload.comment: A standard code indicating the priority of this admission or visit. (837I 2300/CL101)

payload.name: inst_admit_source_std_id
payload.comment: A standard code indicating the source of the referral for the admission or visit. (837I 2300/CL102)

payload.name: inst_discharge_status_std_id
payload.comment: A standard code indicating the status of the patient as of the statement end date. (837I 2300/CL103)

payload.name: inst_type_of_bill_std_id
payload.comment: A standard code identifying the type of facility where services were performed. (837I 2300/CLM05-01, CLM05-03)

payload.name: inst_drg_std_id
payload.comment: A standard diagnosis-related group code indicating the payment classification. (837I 2300/HCP06)

payload.name: place_of_service_std_id
payload.comment: A standard code indicating the facility or place where services were rendered, as maintained by the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services (CMS). (2400/SV105)

payload.name: service_line_number
payload.comment: An integer representing the sequence for this service line within the claim. (2400/LX01)

payload.name: diagnosis_code_qual
payload.comment: The type of code used to indicate the disease, injury, or condition. Examples: ICD-10, ICD-9.

payload.name: admit_diagnosis_ind
payload.comment: A flag indicating whether the diagnosis reported on an institutional claim represents the admitting diagnosis. (2300/HI01-02)

payload.name: procedure_code_qual
payload.comment: The type of code used to indicate the course of action taken by the healthcare practitioner. Examples: CPT, HCPCS. (837P 2400/SV101-01; 837I 2400/SV202-01)

payload.name: procedure_units_billed
payload.comment: The number of discrete actions, elements, or precisely measured amounts administered in this course of action. (837P 2400/SV104; 837I 2400/SV205)

payload.name: procedure_modifier_1
payload.comment: Identifies the first qualifier for the procedure code. This is a code that supplies additional information about the procedure. (837P 2400/SV101-03; 837I 2400/SV202-03)

payload.name: procedure_modifier_2
payload.comment: Identifies the second qualifier for the procedure code. This is a code that supplies additional information about the procedure. (837P 2400/SV101-04; 837I 2400/SV202-04)

payload.name: procedure_modifier_3
payload.comment: Identifies the third qualifier for the procedure code. This is a code that supplies additional information about the procedure. (837P 2400/SV101-05; 837I 2400/SV202-05)

payload.name: procedure_modifier_4
payload.comment: Identifies the fourth qualifier for the procedure code. This is a code that supplies additional information about the procedure. (837P 2400/SV101-06; 837I 2400/SV202-06)

payload.name: revenue_code
payload.comment: A standard NUBC revenue code from the UB claim form. (837I 2400/SV201)

payload.name: line_charge
payload.comment: The total amount charged for this service line. (837P 2400/SV102; 837I 2400/SV203)

payload.name: line_allowed
payload.comment: The total amount allowed for this service line. (2400/HCP02)

payload.name: prov_rendering_npi
payload.comment: The standard National Provider Identifier (NPI) for the provider who rendered services. (837P 2310B-2420A/NM109, NM108=XX; 837I 2310D-2420C/NM109, NM108=XX)

payload.name: prov_billing_npi
payload.comment: The standard National Provider Identifier (NPI) for the provider that billed for services. (2010AA/NM109, NM108=XX)

payload.name: prov_referring_npi
payload.comment: The standard National Provider Identifier (NPI) for the provider who referred the patient to the rendering provider. (837P 2310A/NM109, NM108=XX; 837I 2310F/NM109, NM108=XX)

payload.name: payer_type
payload.comment: A code indicating the classification for the payer.

payload.name: prov_rendering_std_taxonomy
payload.comment: The National Uniform Claim Committee (NUCC) standard taxonomy code for the provider who rendered services. (837P 2310B/PRV03; 837I 2310D/PRV03)

payload.name: prov_billing_std_taxonomy
payload.comment: The National Uniform Claim Committee (NUCC) standard taxonomy code for the provider who submitted the claim. (2000A/PRV03)

payload.name: prov_referring_std_taxonomy
payload.comment: The National Uniform Claim Committee (NUCC) standard taxonomy code for the provider who referred the patient to the rendering provider.
